==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Teache
<hw>Teache</hw> <pr>(t⟦emac⟧ch)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Amer. Sp.
<ets>tacha</ets>, <ets>tacho</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Sugar Manuf.)</fld>
<def>Any one of the series of boilers or evaporating pans in which the
cane juice is concentrated in making sugar; especially, the last boiler
of the series.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>The 1890 edition had the following etymology for
<ex>teache</ex>: <ety>[Cf. Ir. <ets>teaghaim</ets>, Gael.
<ets>teasaich</ets>, to heat.]</ety>. Presumably a speculation which
proved incorrect?</note></p>

<p><ent>Teacher</ent>⟦br⟧
